</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shehbahn>shehbahn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/4/02 2:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=284.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Islamic Fundamentalism?</span><hr size=1> The article attempts to analyse global trends - focusing on highly mediatised inviduals is outside the scope. Looking at OBL as a "control sample" to validate or invalidate the arguments is moot. His own beliefs are irrelevant, only his message is of consequence. His arrest / execution would make him a perfect canditate to martyrdom.<br>
<br>
Other than that, the article presents a very interesting new line of lateral thinking. The conclusions though would greatly benefit from some factual numbers (as pointed out in a previous reply). The fundamentalist flare could also be interpreted as a backlash to encroaching western culture imposing the separation of church and state, which is perceived, and probably rightfully so, as what caused the decline of the secular christian faith.<br>
<br>
